06-22-2017/ Judge M Joseph Donald                  
It is hereby stipulated by the respective parties that the sentence which was imposed in the above-captioned matter on July 1, 2015, be modified as follows:    
The Initial Confinement portion of the sentence shall  be modified to two (2) years, and, factoring in both the pre-sentence credit which the defendant was granted at the time of sentencing, and the amount of time he has already spent in custody since the date of sentencing, the Initial Confinement term shall be deemed to have been fully satisfied,  and the defendant shall therefore be ordered released from custody forthwith.      

It is further stipulated that Extended Supervision portion of the sentence shall be modified to two (2) years.

Letter from Attorney Patrick Cavanaugh Brennan filing a Bail Assignment.

Defendant Antonio M Barbour in court with attorney Patrick Cavanaugh Brennan.  Defendant Antonio M Barbour in custody.  Michael Thurston appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Statements made as to Sentencing by both counsel and Defendant.  Also present in court Detective Vince Fonte (MPD).  

COURT SENTENCED Defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 9 YEARS, with credit for 51 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 5 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 4 YEARS. 

 The defendant  IS NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration AND the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Programs.

COURT ORDERED THE FOLLOWING CONDITIONS AS TO THE EXTENDED SUPERVISION ARE AS FOLLOWS:
*  No new law violations reaching the level of a probable cause finding.
*  Pay costs, surcharges assessments supervision, Victim Witness, DNA fees out of bail on deposit, if any. If not Defendant shall pay up to 25% of prison funds with the balance due prior to the end of the Extended Supervision.  Failure to pay shall result in a Civil Judgment with tax intercept.
* 1st  Restitution $534.10 to the victim's mother Leslie Love out of bail on deposit, if any. If not Defendant shall pay up to 25% of prison funds with the balance due prior to the end of the Extended Supervision.  Failure to pay shall result in a Civil Judgment with tax intercept.
*  No contact with the victim Z.L., unless in the presence of another adult.
*  Defendant required to provide a biological specimen (DNA) to the State Crime Lab.
*  As a convicted felon Defendant shall NEVER be in possession of any firearms /body armor / weapons at any time in the future.
*  Defendant can't vote in any election until civil rights are restored.
*  MUST cooperate with the Sex Offender Reporting Requirements under Wisconsin Stats. 301.45.
*  MUST cooperate Sex offender treatment and and any other programming deemed appropriate by the Department and or agent.
*  Defendant is ordered not to work with children nor volunteering in any organizations involving children under the age of 16.
